</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0334-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0334-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>Letter not found, but see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-09-02-0329" class="document">Adam to GW, 9 January</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0334-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0334-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>James Cleveland had been overseer of River farm at Mount Vernon since 1765, and in 1775 GW sent him out to his lands on the Great Kanawha where with GWs workers in the summer and fall he made the improvements required by law. See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-10-02-0165" class="document">GW to Cleveland, 10 Jan. 1775</a>, and references to his agreement with Cleveland of the same date in <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-10-02-0165&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-10-02-0165-fn-0006#GEWN-02-10-02-0165-fn-0006" class="document">note <span class="choice correction" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover_choice ] header=[]  body=[ Corrected from '5' &lt;span style='font-size: 90%'&gt;[[2007-01-24]]&lt;/span&gt; ]">6</span></a>, and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-10-02-0278" class="document">Cleveland to GW, 12</a>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-10-02-0280" class="document">21 May</a>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-10-02-0283" class="document">7 June</a>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-02-02-0350" class="document">16 Nov. 1775</a>. See also <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-09-02-0329&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-09-02-0329-fn-0002#GEWN-02-09-02-0329-fn-0002" class="document">Robert Adam to GW, 9 Jan. 1774, n.2</a>. Mr. Thompson is Richard Thompson (see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-09-02-0264" class="document">his letter to GW, 30 Sept. 1773</a>).</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0334-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0334-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>No letter from Dr. David Ross has been found.</p>

</div>
